    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>One way of doing this is to do add junit.jar to your <code>$CLASSPATH</code> as an external dependency.</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/0UiY8.gif\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/0UiY8.gif\" alt=\"adding junit intellij\"></a></p>\n\n<p>So to do that, go to project structure, and then add JUnit as one of the libraries as shown in the gif.</p>\n\n<p>In the 'Choose Modules' prompt choose only the modules that you'd need JUnit for.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 273736,
      "reputation" : 16571,
